%N A395940 Decimal expansion of the median distance between two points independently and uniformly selected at random one on each of two adjacent faces of a unit cube.
%C A395940 The smallest positive root of the equation 8*x^3 - 3*x^4 - 12/Pi = 0.
%H A395940 Arak M. Mathai, Peter Moschopoulos, and Giorgio Pederzoli, <a href="https://rivista-statistica.unibo.it/article/view/1104">Distance between random points in a cube</a>, Statistica, Vol. 59, No. 1 (1999), pp. 61-81; <a href="https://www.researchgate.net/publication/268489321">ResearchGate link</a>.
%H A395940 Eric Weisstein's World of Mathematics, <a href="https://mathworld.wolfram.com/CubeLinePickingFaceandFace.html">Cube Line Picking--Face and Face</a>.
%H A395940 <a href="/index/Tra#transcendental">Index entries for transcendental numbers</a>.
%e A395940 0.8958753280867109826678828315777710608840272477561609...
%t A395940 RealDigits[x /. FindRoot[8*x^3 - 3*x^4 - 12/Pi, {x, 1}, WorkingPrecision -> 120]][[1]]
%o A395940 (PARI) solve(x = 0.8, 1, 8*x^3 - 3*x^4 - 12/Pi)
%Y A395940 Cf. A395017, A395938 (mean), A395939 (opposite faces).
%K A395940 nonn,cons,new
